<section sectnbr = "2B">
<servcat sctnbr = "02" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B2206004" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Front Strut Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B2206003">Front Strut Assembly Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
When compressing coil spring, observe the following points to avoid personal injury.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Attach spring compressor to coil spring securely.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not use impact wrench for compressing it.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Use commercially available spring compressor strictly following manufacturer’s instructions.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention1>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Strut support lower nut is precoated with friction stabilizer. Do not reuse nut, otherwise nut may loosen.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B2206004001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Attach special tool (A) to coil spring as shown. Screw in special tool bolts (1) alternately until coil spring tension is released from strut. Rotate strut to confirm that it is free of coil spring tension.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L2B001">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09943-25010">
09943–25010
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.310mm" ver = "02" gw = "188" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
While keeping coil spring compressed using special tool, remove strut support lower nut using hexagon wrench as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A220008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.511mm" ver = "01" gw = "98" gh = "112"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disassemble front strut assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B2206004002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Compress coil spring using special tool (spring compressor) until total length “a” becomes about 260 mm (10.2 in.).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L2B002">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09943-25010">
09943–25010
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<spec>
<title>
Length
</title>
<ptxt>
“a”: About 260 mm (10.2 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.428mm" ver = "02" gw = "158" gh = "107"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.407in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.280in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.416in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[u]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Upper side (large diameter)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[l]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Lower side (small diameter)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install compressed coil spring to front strut by fitting coil spring end (2) onto spring lower seat (1) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Spring end should not ride on step in spring lower seat.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220010.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.318mm" ver = "01" gw = "206" gh = "132"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set bump stopper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set strut dust cover (1) over three claws (2) of damper cap (3).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.821mm" ver = "02" gw = "209" gh = "130"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull strut rod as far up as possible and use care not to allow it to retract into strut.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install coil spring upper seat.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install strut bearing, strut bearing plate, strut support and new strut support lower nut in this sequence. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Then tighten strut support lower nut to specified torque while holding stud using hexagon wrench.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B005">
<t-part>
Strut support lower nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
50
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
37.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220038.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.480mm" ver = "01" gw = "188" gh = "124"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove special tool (spring compressor) from coil spring.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
